The Schezwan Chicken Lollipops are to die for. They are so crispy and the flavour is top notch. The quantity and size is filling as well

These Cheesy Chicken Momos are beautifully crunchy. The pricing for 8 momos is a steal deal.

I personally don't like banana, but I was bold and ordered the Banana Nutella Pancakes and I was in awe. I can't believe I devoured Bananas Pancakes.

This was truly a delightful dinning experience. I am definitely coming back here to try their other menu options and definitely recommending it to my friends.

The owner and the staff is very well mannered and sweet. There is nice parking opposite the restaurant and a beautiful view of the river. The quantity of food for the price is very reasonable. Thank You.

description:
**The Bodhi Tree Cafe and Bar: A Hidden Gem in Mandrem**

Nestled in the serene landscape of Mandrem, The Bodhi Tree Cafe and Bar has captured the hearts of locals and travelers alike, boasting an impressive rating of 4.8 from over 4,600 reviews. With a menu rich in **Tibetan food**, this inviting eatery is particularly known for its **thupka**, **udon**, and **tingmo**â€”items that have contributed significantly to their popularity among diners yearning for unique culinary experiences.

### Ambiance & Design

Stepping into The Bodhi Tree is like entering a peaceful oasis. The dÃ©cor exudes a whimsical charm, characterized by warm, inviting colors, lush greenery, and rustic wooden features that instantly make guests feel at home. The lighting is soft and relaxing, creating an atmosphere perfect for both casual dining and intimate gatherings. The outdoor area, with a stunning view of the surrounding river, adds a picturesque backdrop to your meal, making it an ideal spot to unwind and enjoy good food.

Images shared by patrons exemplify this vibe; you'll notice charming spots perfectly set for relaxation, complete with cozy seating arrangements ideal for soaking up the gentle Mandrem breeze. The friendly presence of local animals, as mentioned by families with children, further enhances the welcoming ambiance.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The Bodhi Tree's menu is a delightful array of unique offerings that stand out for both their flavor and presentation. Diners rave about the **Schezwan Chicken Lollipops**â€”crispy and bursting with flavor, they are a must-try for anyone visiting. The **Cheesy Chicken Momos** also receive high praise, noted for their delectable crunch and generous portion size that promises satisfaction for your palate. For those with a sweet tooth, the **Banana Nutella Pancakes** have earned a special mention, transforming even the most banana-cautious diners into fans.

The restaurant does not just focus on traditional dishes; it also excels in accommodating dietary preferences, making it a versatile choice for various dietary needs. The portion sizes are generous, ensuring great value for money, and the pricing is highlighted as affordable across several reviews.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer experience at The Bodhi Tree is elevated by the attentive and friendly service provided by the staff. Reviewers consistently mention the mannerism of the owner and team, who go out of their way to ensure a pleasant dining experience. The welcoming atmosphere paired with efficient service enhances the overall enjoyment of a meal here. While specifics about reservation policies weren't detailed, the positive sentiment around their walk-in accommodations makes it an accessible choice for spontaneous diners.

### Popularity & Reviews

The Bodhi Tree has also gained traction on social media, with many guests sharing their experiences online, which adds to its buzz as a go-to destination. While the culinary offerings may not push boundaries for those seeking truly avant-garde flavors, they excel in delivering a fulfilling dining experience that many find comforting and satisfying.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The restaurant's charm comes through vividly in the photographs shared by diners. The images reveal a beautifully presented space that blends nature with thoughtful dining arrangements, and the food looks equally invitingâ€”from the vibrant colors of the momos to the enticing drizzles on the pancakes. Each shot encapsulates both the essence of the cafÃ© and its delicious culinary highlights, inviting new patrons to share in the experience.

In conclusion, The Bodhi Tree Cafe and Bar stands as a beacon for those in Mandrem seeking a delightful blend of Tibetan flavors, welcoming ambiance, and genuine service. Whether you're drawn in by the menu or the idyllic riverside setting, this cafe promises a fulfilling experience that will keep you coming back for more.
